The paper discusses the use of download and reference manager data for research evaluation and library collection development, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category as it directly relates to the topic of academic publications and online repositories. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval of information from large datasets, which is a key aspect of analyzing readership data. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible sub-category as the paper touches on the social implications of readership data. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible sub-categories as they both involve analyzing data and information flow.
